id: pm-2n6i
title: pm next should skip completed open containers when recommending actionable work
description: "Regression follow-up for pm next: the command advertises ready work as active leaves with no open children, but current output recommends open Epics/containers whose children are already 100 percent closed before actionable leaf work. Fix ranking/filtering so agent loops get concrete work first while still exposing completed containers as governance context when useful."
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-ux,"area:cli",context-management
created_at: "2026-06-26T04:53:53.825Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-26T05:12:42.841Z"
author: codex-gpt5-pm-next-20260626
estimated_minutes: 90
acceptance_criteria: pm next does not recommend open containers that have children_total > 0 and children_closed == children_total ahead of actionable leaf items; output remains token-efficient and documents any completed-container governance signal; focused tests cover the regression.
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Resolved the pm next ranking regression by demoting otherwise-ready completed containers behind concrete leaf work while preserving them as governance closeout rows.
expected_result: pm next recommends active concrete leaf work before 100%-complete open containers and documents completed-container closeout behavior across CLI docs and MCP contracts.
actual_result: "pm next now ranks concrete leaf entries ahead of completed containers, adds a completed-container governance closeout rationale when such a row is recommended, updates docs/MCP contract text, and passes focused tests, contracts, full coverage, temp smoke, security, changelog, and observability gates."
comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
